        "action": "Abolish jury trials and let judges rule on cases",
        "additional_details": "",
        "background": "The idea that a jury can make vital decisions in a trial is absurd. The judge is fully qualified in their position and should be trusted ; whilst the members of the jury may give a perfectly rational opinion , they are often biased due to their own religious and moral views.",
